for
the
sake
of
discovering
them."
"If
you
will
thank
me,"
he
replied,
"let
it
be
for
yourself
alone.
That
the
wish
of
giving
happiness
to
you
might
add
force
to
the
other
inducements
which
led
me
on,
I
shall
not
attempt
to
deny.
But
your
family
owe
me
nothing.
Much
as
I
respect
them,
I
believe
I
thought
only
of
you."
Elizabeth
was
too
much
embarrassed
to
say
a
word.
After
a
short
