her
companion
added,
"You
are
too
generous
to
trifle
with
me.
If
your
feelings
are
still
what
they
were
last
April,
tell
me
so
at
once.
My
affections
and
wishes
are
unchanged,
but
one
word
from
you
will
silence
me
on
this
subject
for
ever."
Elizabeth,
feeling
all
the
more
than
common
awkwardness
and
anxiety
of
his
situation,
now
forced
herself
to
speak;
and
immediately,
though
